Uh, gonna leave all this to Vi and the girls

165
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,490
如果你不想要的话
if you're not interested.

166
00:10:22,980 --> 00:10:24,440
外婆的首饰
Grandmother's jewelry?

167
00:10:26,450 --> 00:10:28,900
要是我不至少跟你提一嘴
She'd turn over in her grave

168
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:30,790
她在墓里都得气翻身
if I didn't at least offer it to you.

169
00:10:32,090 --> 00:10:33,470
她品味真不错
She had great taste. 

170
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:36,790
不然你以为我的品味从哪来的
Where do you think I got it from?

171
00:10:39,830 --> 00:10:40,870
这是什么
What's this?

172
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:47,360
你打开看看吧
Look at it. Open it up.

173
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:55,340
肯定还是值点钱的  第一夫人的乳牙
Must be worth somethin', baby teeth of the First Lady.

174
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:00,060
我挺喜欢那个小伙儿
I like that boy.

175
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,660
能让我笑出来
Makes me laugh.

176
00:11:04,350 --> 00:11:06,180
和你父亲在世的时候一样
Like your father used to.

177
00:11:06,330 --> 00:11:10,010
我想象不出父亲扮成算命的是什么样
Can't imagine daddy dressed up as a fortune teller.

178
00:11:10,010 --> 00:11:14,560
你意想不到  他也有逗比的一面
Oh, you'd be surprised. He had a silly side to him.

179
00:11:15,130 --> 00:11:16,550
我是没见过
Not that I ever saw.

180
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:23,930
有些事他只会在我面前做
Well, there were certain things that he only did with me.

181
00:11:31,010 --> 00:11:33,870
你瞧  笑一笑能缓解疼痛
Oh, you see, laughter is good for the pain.

182
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:37,560
比吗啡还有效
Even better than this morphine.

183
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:41,030
-我来帮你吧  -不用  我自己能行
- Let me help you. - No, no, I can do it.

184
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:42,400
你走吧
You just go.

185
00:11:45,540 --> 00:11:46,480
走
Go!

186
00:12:06,010 --> 00:12:07,400
你把所有内容都划掉了
You crossed everything out.

187
00:12:09,330 --> 00:12:12,210
-因为不够好  -我知道
- It wasn't good. - I know.

188
00:12:18,780 --> 00:12:21,690
等她去世了  你打算对这里也那样吗
Is that what you're gonna do here, after she dies?

189
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:26,880
因为不够好  把一切都抹去
Cross everything out... because it wasn't good?

190
00:12:32,060 --> 00:12:34,370
我不会和你谈论我母亲的
You're not going to get me to talk about my mother.

191
00:12:38,190 --> 00:12:39,420
我希望不会
I hope not.

192
00:12:40,340 --> 00:12:41,650
恨太丑陋了
Hatred's ugly.

193
00:12:42,290 --> 00:12:44,140
天气这么好  不适合谈那个
It's too beautiful a day for that.

194
00:12:46,390 --> 00:12:47,670
回去干活儿喽
Back to the salt mines.

195
00:12:58,750 --> 00:12:59,850
请坐
Please, sit.

196
00:13:00,530 --> 00:13:02,720
先生  这是哈里发国目前的位置
Sir, these are the current ICO positions.

197
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:04,500
我们还在起草任务项目
We're still drafting action items,

198
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:05,800
但是我们可给您一个大致的
but we can give you a rough sense--

199
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:08,280
在讨论军事选择之前
Well, before we discuss any military options,

200
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:11,390
我要和大马士革通话  看看他们能允许什么行动
I'd like to put a call in to Damascus and see what they'll allow.

201
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:14,220
国务卿女士  跟我一起来吧
Madam Secretary, won't you join me?

202
00:13:20,880 --> 00:13:23,290
为了单独见我  你不惜召集
So you had to call a national security meeting

203
00:13:23,290 --> 00:13:24,830
国家安全会议
just to get us in the same room?

204
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:27,180
也为了不让你和康威通话
And to keep you off the phone with Conway.

205
00:13:27,180 --> 00:13:30,100
我只需要给他打一通电话  不需要第二通
All I needed was one call to him. I don't need to make another.

206
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:31,130
你不会真觉得
You don't actually think

207
00:13:31,130 --> 00:13:33,330
他会任命你为国务卿吧
he's gonna make you Secretary of State, do you?

208
00:13:33,330 --> 00:13:35,580
估计不会  但我真想看到
Probably not, but I would've paid good money

209
00:13:35,580 --> 00:13:38,410
他告诉你那消息时你的脸色
just to see your face when he told you.

210
00:13:38,410 --> 00:13:39,890
我从没保证要和你一起参选
I never promised you the ticket.

211
00:13:39,890 --> 00:13:41,440
我只说了会尽力
I promised you I'd try.

212
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:43,410
你尽力都是装的
You pretended to try.

213
00:13:43,420 --> 00:13:45,480
对克莱尔的支持不会凭空出现
Claire's support didn't just happen on its own,

214
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:48,170
你还有胆量握着我的手
and you had the gall to take my hand,

215
00:13:48,170 --> 00:13:51,100
看着我的眼睛  对我撒谎
look me in the eye and lie to my face.

216
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:54,000
-你错了  凯茜  -拜托  弗兰克
- You're mistaken, Cathy. - Oh, come on, Frank.

217
00:13:54,190 --> 00:13:56,000
从沃克上台的那天起
I've had a front row seat to everything

218
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,180
我就近距离看到了一切
since the day Walker took office,

219
00:13:58,180 --> 00:14:01,490
所有的谎言和背叛  我还帮了你
all the lies and betrayals, and I helped you.

220
00:14:01,490 --> 00:14:04,310
我的错误是以为你不会在背后捅我一刀
My mistake was I assumed you wouldn't stab me in the back.

221
00:14:04,310 --> 00:14:07,800
你的错误是弄巧成拙
Your mistake is that it backfired.

222
00:14:09,710 --> 00:14:11,960
这完全是个人恩怨  对吧
This is all personal, isn't it?

223
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:15,260
完全是为了报复我在医院时  克莱尔那样对你
This is about how Claire treated you when I was in the hospital.

224
00:14:15,260 --> 00:14:17,840
别这么小瞧我  这是生意
Give me more credit than that. This is business.

225
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:20,260
我们曾是合作伙伴  是你违约了
We were partners. You broke the contract.

226
00:14:20,260 --> 00:14:24,240
-那你想要什么  -你还有什么呢  弗兰克
- So, what do you want? - What else is there, Frank?

227
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:26,040
什么都没了
Nothing.

228
00:14:27,770 --> 00:14:31,110
很简单  要么让克莱尔的选票改投给我
It's simple. Either Claire's votes come my way...

229
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:33,990
要么我就把大会搞得一团糟
or I turn the convention upside down.

230
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:39,120
我们得谈谈赛斯
We need to talk about Seth.

231
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:41,420
我从前客户那里接到了许多电话
I've been getting calls from former clients.

232
00:14:41,690 --> 00:14:44,720
你开口之前  我告诉你我干过的坏事吧
Now, before you say anything, here's the dirt.

233
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:46,980
我8年级时在一个数学测验上做过弊
I cheated on a math test in 8th grade,

234
00:14:46,980 --> 00:14:49,870
我16岁时曾偷过一条返校节裙子
I shoplifted a homecoming dress when I was 16,

235
00:14:49,870 --> 00:14:52,290
我大一时跟一个女生联谊会的姐妹搞过
I experimented with a sorority sister in freshman year,

236
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:54,530
我2007年晚交了税
and I was late on my taxes in 2007.

237
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:59,360
但他不会找到任何开除我的正当理由
What he won't find is anything that justifies firing me.

238
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:02,260
他肯定只是在审查你  我们对每个人都要审查
I'm sure he was just vetting you. We do that with everyone.

239
00:15:03,730 --> 00:15:05,590
你非要这样说的话  那好吧
Okay, if that's your story, then fine,

240
00:15:05,590 --> 00:15:07,570
但我只在乎赢得大选
but all I care about is winning this election.

241
00:15:07,570 --> 00:15:10,830
我们放下个人恩怨  团结起来  好吗
So let's get past our personal shit and be a team, okay?

242
00:15:15,950 --> 00:15:18,180
我们在对抗同一个敌人  总统先生
We're fighting a common enemy here, Mr. President.

243
00:15:18,180 --> 00:15:20,470
我们保持团结十分重要
It's important that we remain united.

244
00:15:20,470 --> 00:15:23,350
嗯  我向你保证我们采取任何行动前
Yeah, and I can assure you that Secretary Durant will reach out

245
00:15:23,350 --> 00:15:25,490
杜兰特国务卿都会跟你联系
before we conduct any operation.

246
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:26,840
非常感谢  总统先生
Thank you for your time, Mr. President.

247
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:29,460
我们一想出计划就会联系你
We'll be in touch as soon as we come up with a plan.

248
00:15:29,790 --> 00:15:32,130
你演得好像我还能当国务卿似的
You're acting like I'll still be Secretary of State.

249
00:15:32,130 --> 00:15:34,510
如果你决策正确  就会是的
Well, if you play your cards right, you will be.

250
00:15:34,510 --> 00:15:36,700
你还请过谁当你的副总统
Who else did you offer the VP slot to?

251
00:15:36,700 --> 00:15:38,880
杰姬  奥斯汀  我  还有谁
There's Jackie, Austen, me. Anyone else?

252
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:41,230
奥斯汀自愿退出的  杰姬也是
Austen withdrew on his own, and so did Jackie.

253
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,910
我没有逼她退出
I did not push her out.

254
00:15:42,910 --> 00:15:44,690
杰姬说你视她如无物
Jackie says you took her for granted,

255
00:15:44,690 --> 00:15:47,000
说你威胁她  恐吓她
that you bullied her, you intimidated her.

256
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:49,550
她正在给加州的代表们
And that is what she is telling every member

257
00:15:49,550 --> 00:15:53,490
一个一个打电话说这件事
of the California delegation, one phone call at a time.

258
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:55,920
加州  票很多
California. Lots of votes.

259
00:15:56,580 --> 00:15:59,260
加州  民主党大会最大的票仓
California, the largest piece of delegates at the Democratic Convention.

260
00:15:59,260 --> 00:16:02,290
我听说代表团正在倾向希瑟·邓巴
I'm told that delegation is trending toward Heather Dunbar.

261
00:16:02,290 --> 00:16:03,180
来看一下  沃尔夫
Let's watch this, Wolf.

262
00:16:03,180 --> 00:16:05,120
想像一下她只拿下
Let's imagine she only picked up

263
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:06,580
加州三分之二的代表
two-thirds of the California delegates.

264
00:16:06,580 --> 00:16:07,990
这样就超过300票了
That gets you above 300 there.

265
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,880
另外  我们估计她能守住她家乡康涅狄格州
Plus, we assume she'll keep her home state Connecticut's support.

266
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:11,700
这样起点就相当不错
Off to a pretty good start.

267
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:15,080
超过300代表选票  大概是7%的选票了
It's over 300 delegates. What, roughly, uh, 7% of the vote?

268
00:16:15,090 --> 00:16:17,540
单单这些就可以进入到...第二轮投票了吧
That alone could take this, what, to a second ballot?

269
00:16:17,550 --> 00:16:19,910
可以使她进入第二轮投票  又是开放代表大会
That takes it to a second ballot, an open convention again.

270
00:16:19,910 --> 00:16:20,980
而且我们预计
Plus, we also assume that

271
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:23,430
路易斯安那州会继续支持凯瑟琳·杜兰特
Louisiana will stay with Catherine Durant.

272
00:16:23,430 --> 00:16:25,790
至少在第一轮投票结束前
So, we are not going to have a definitive idea

273
00:16:25,790 --> 00:16:27,310
我们无法确切了解
of how all this is gonna shape up

274
00:16:27,430 --> 00:16:28,880
局势将如何走向
at least until they conduct the first ballot.

275
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:30,860
目前总统和杜兰特国务卿
There's still no update as to, uh,

276
00:16:30,860 --> 00:16:33,910
将何时返程还没有新的消息
when the president and Secretary Durant will return.

277
00:16:33,910 --> 00:16:35,450
没有  这也增加了不确定性
No, and that adds to some of the uncertainty here.

278
00:16:35,450 --> 00:16:37,720
我们回到现场  看看情况如何
So let's go back to the floor, see how things are playing out.

279
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:39,060
文章里没有明确
It didn't specify in the article

280
00:16:39,060 --> 00:16:41,380
当时车队朝哪个方向开的
which direction the motorcade was heading.

281
00:16:44,880 --> 00:16:45,840
朝东
East.

282
00:16:47,130 --> 00:16:49,780
{\an8}贝茨城
东

283
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:49,470
你确定吗
You're sure?

284
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:52,960
非常感谢
Thank you very much.

285
00:17:09,690 --> 00:17:15,890
{\an8}贝茨市葡萄园

286
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:17,960
我去
Hot damn!

287
00:17:19,050 --> 00:17:22,560
我保证你想当多久国务卿都可以
I am promising you Secretary of State for as long as you want it

288
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:26,400
你2024年竞选总统时我会全力支持
and my full support when you run for President in 2024.

289
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:28,040
谁知道呢  你说不好会走运
I mean, who knows, you might even get lucky.

290
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:29,670
我的肝脏在那之前说不定就衰竭了
My liver might fail before then.

291
00:17:29,670 --> 00:17:31,220
你把我的职位许给贝克的时候
Your promises stopped meaning much

292
00:17:31,220 --> 00:17:33,530
你的承诺就没有意义了
after you promised Baker my job.

293
00:17:33,540 --> 00:17:35,960
我并没打算让他当国务卿
I have no intention of offering him Secretary of State.

294
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:38,690
所以你就像沃克骗你一样骗了他
Oh, so you lied to him the way Walker lied to you.

295
00:17:38,690 --> 00:17:41,730
不  我和沃克又不是老交情
No. Walker and I didn't have a history.

296
00:17:41,740 --> 00:17:43,930
沃克也不尊重我
And Walker didn't respect me.

297
00:17:43,930 --> 00:17:47,560
你我是有交情的  凯茜  我也非常尊重你
You and I have a history, Cathy, and I respect you immensely.

298
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:50,370
但是我们共事才3年
But our history goes back three years.

299
00:17:50,370 --> 00:17:53,200
克莱尔和我已经是30年的搭档了
Claire's and my partnership goes back 30.

300
00:17:53,210 --> 00:17:55,110
你必须尊重这一点
You have to respect that.

301
00:17:55,110 --> 00:17:56,210
我可能会...
I might have...

302
00:17:56,980 --> 00:17:59,420
如果你一开始就对我说实话的话
if you had been honest with me from the beginning.

303
00:17:59,430 --> 00:18:02,660
我希望时间能倒退  可我们现在已经这样了
Well, I wish I could turn back time, but here we are.

304
00:18:02,660 --> 00:18:05,030
你可以把我挡在亚特兰大之外  想多久多久
And you can keep me out of Atlanta for as long as you want,

305
00:18:05,030 --> 00:18:07,430
但你不能永远拖着选票
but you can't hold the vote back forever.

306
00:18:07,670 --> 00:18:11,810
时间在前进不是倒退  而时间在我这边
Time's moving forward, not back. And time is on my side.

307
00:18:16,660 --> 00:18:19,690
如果希瑟·邓巴想占总统不在的便宜
If Heather Dunbar wants to take advantage of the President's absence, 

308
00:18:19,690 --> 00:18:20,950
那是她的权利
that's her prerogative.

309
00:18:20,950 --> 00:18:23,400
但是她仍在华府  而且没有发表公开声明
But she's still in D.C., there's no public statement.

310
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:25,520
你认为这是占便宜
You see that as taking advantage?

311
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:28,340
你认为如果不是她在华府幕后操纵
You think Congresswoman Sharp would make calls on her behalf

312
00:18:28,340 --> 00:18:30,460
夏普议员会代表她打电话拉票吗
if she wasn't pulling the strings from Washington?

313
00:18:30,460 --> 00:18:32,480
夏普说是她自己打的
Sharp says she's doing it on her own.

314
00:18:32,670 --> 00:18:34,980
你没有任何证据表明她们有合作
You don't have any proof of coordination.

315
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:36,830
你说得对  我没有
You're right, I don't. 

316
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:38,660
只是凭人性  基本逻辑
Just human nature, basic logic, 

317
00:18:38,660 --> 00:18:40,400
还有比常人多一点
and a slightly better than average understanding

318
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:42,140
对政治手腕的了解
of political gamesmanship.

319
00:18:42,550 --> 00:18:46,820
失陪一下  新闻发言人也要上厕所
Uh, if you will excuse me, even press secretaries have to pee.

320
00:18:46,820 --> 00:18:47,980
-我马上回来  -好的
- I'll just be right back. - Okay.

321
00:18:47,980 --> 00:18:50,400
失陪  抱歉  失陪
Excuse me. Excuse me. I'm sorry. Excuse me.

322
00:18:54,830 --> 00:18:55,750
怎么了
What's up?

323
00:18:57,120 --> 00:19:00,210
莉安知道了  我认为是你告诉了她
LeAnn knows, and I think you told her.

324
00:19:00,210 --> 00:19:03,030
对  直截了当  我全告诉她了
I did. Straight up. I told her everything.

325
00:19:03,220 --> 00:19:05,200
-走  上楼去  -不
- Let's go. Upstairs. - No.

326
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:09,250
-你说什么  -邓巴重回游戏
- Excuse me? - You've got Dunbar in play,

327
00:19:09,250 --> 00:19:10,940
杜兰特和总统在一起
you got Durant with the President,

328
00:19:10,940 --> 00:19:12,460
第一夫人在达拉斯
and the First Lady's in Dallas.

329
00:19:12,460 --> 00:19:13,580
这儿有一屋子记者
And I've got a room full of press

330
00:19:13,580 --> 00:19:15,130
我从早上八点就在这儿应付他们
that I've been keeping at bay since 8:00 this morning,

331
00:19:15,130 --> 00:19:17,630
等我把熊孩子都哄睡了
so I will tell you why I told her...

332
00:19:18,060 --> 00:19:20,410
再跟你讲你我为什么告诉她吧
after I tuck in all the children.

333
00:19:48,410 --> 00:19:55,130
现在投票
Let's vote now!

334
00:19:55,130 --> 00:19:56,650
请安静一下
Order, please!

335
00:19:57,820 --> 00:20:00,900
现在请希尔参议员讲话
It is Senator Sheer's time to speak.

336
00:20:01,980 --> 00:20:02,920
安静
Order!

337
00:20:03,670 --> 00:20:06,130
也许我们应该让凯茜得逞
Maybe we should let Cathy have her way.

338
00:20:06,930 --> 00:20:10,700
如果现在投票  你们获胜  我们大选再战
If the vote's held now, you two win. We focus on the general.

339
00:20:11,940 --> 00:20:13,400
为什么这么说
What's brought all this on?

340
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:17,840
我只是在想我们这么做
I just wonder if we're in over our heads,

341
00:20:17,840 --> 00:20:19,560
是不是不自量力  弗兰西斯
Francis, trying to do this.

342
00:20:20,470 --> 00:20:21,890
是你母亲吗
Is it your mother?

343
00:20:21,890 --> 00:20:24,170
看到她病得这么重一定很不好受吧
I'm sure it's difficult to see her this sick.

344
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:29,640
她完全无助
She's completely helpless.

345
00:20:30,050 --> 00:20:33,340
但我们并不无助  我们可以扭转局势
But we're not helpless. We can turn this around.

346
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:37,130
我想我只是...
I guess I'm just...

347
00:20:38,900 --> 00:20:42,740
我不知道  也许我们做错了
I don't know, maybe... maybe we're making a mistake.

348
00:20:42,740 --> 00:20:45,180
也许我还没准备好做你的竞选伙伴
Maybe I'm not ready to be your running mate.

349
00:20:45,180 --> 00:20:49,550
-康威有个四星将军  -你母亲快乐吗
- Conway has a four-star general. - Is she happy, your mother?

350
00:20:50,790 --> 00:20:52,340
不  她很痛苦
No, she's miserable.

351
00:20:52,950 --> 00:20:55,430
汤姆逗她笑  但大多数时候不快乐
Tom makes her laugh, but mostly, no.

352
00:20:58,240 --> 00:20:59,920
想象一下我肝衰竭了
Imagine my liver's failing.

353
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:02,230
-想象我要死了  -弗兰西斯
- Imagine I'm dying. - Francis...

354
00:21:02,230 --> 00:21:04,920
不  你就想象一下
No, I just want you to picture it for just a moment.

355
00:21:05,630 --> 00:21:09,100
我躺在床上  像你母亲现在一样
There I am, lying in a bed just like your mother is now.

356
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:12,710
唯一能让我高兴的事
The only thing that would make me happy

357
00:21:12,710 --> 00:21:16,000
就是知道我走了以后  你会接手
is to know that you would take over after I passed.

358
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:18,120
如果是凯茜
If it were Cathy...

359
00:21:18,820 --> 00:21:21,350
我会和你母亲一样痛苦的
I'd be just as miserable as your mother is.

360
00:21:23,150 --> 00:21:24,570
我会做好我的事
I'll do my part.

361
00:21:26,340 --> 00:21:28,660
你就专注你的讲话
You just concentrate on that speech.

362
00:21:30,730 --> 00:21:32,900
好  谢谢你  弗兰西斯
All right. Thank you, Francis.

363
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:33,820
晚安
Good night.

364
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:38,860
-她不吃东西吗  -她吞咽很困难
- She, uh... she won't eat? - It's hard for her to swallow.

365
00:21:40,530 --> 00:21:43,090
你觉得她还有多少时间
How much time do you think she has?

366
00:21:44,550 --> 00:21:49,570
我说不准  可能是几周
I can't be definitive, but... a couple of weeks, maybe.

367
00:21:49,910 --> 00:21:53,150
如果她完全不进食  可能就只有几天了
If she stops eating altogether, it could be days.

368
00:21:54,420 --> 00:21:55,920
她很痛苦
She's in a lot of pain.

369
00:21:58,180 --> 00:21:59,890
她可以不用这么痛苦
She doesn't have to be.

370
00:21:59,890 --> 00:22:03,060
到了这一步  我们可以让她舒适一些
When it gets to this point, we can make her comfortable.

371
00:22:05,640 --> 00:22:08,570
舒适到让她的身体不再挣扎
Comfortable enough that the body will let go.

372
00:22:14,190 --> 00:22:15,420
那是她想要的吗
Does she want that?

373
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:21,220
这个你该和你母亲讨论一下
That is something you should discuss with your mother.

374
00:22:25,650 --> 00:22:27,120
我喜欢那些植物
I like the plants.

375
00:22:28,830 --> 00:22:30,530
你放在那儿的那些
The plants you put in there.

376
00:22:33,670 --> 00:22:35,680
小东西总能让人眼前一亮  对吧
It's the little things, right?

377
00:22:38,660 --> 00:22:39,940
如果我们干掉精炼厂
If we take out the refineries,

378
00:22:39,940 --> 00:22:41,640
就能切断他们的收入来源
that would eliminate their revenue stream.

379
00:22:41,650 --> 00:22:44,070
没有了资源  他们就无法进军
They can't advance if they don't have the resources.

380
00:22:44,070 --> 00:22:46,290
马克宗总统明确表示
President Makhzun made it very clear

381
00:22:46,290 --> 00:22:48,030
不希望精炼厂被毁
he wants those to remain intact.

382
00:22:48,030 --> 00:22:50,510
从战略角度看  那是我们最好的选择
It's our best option from a strategic point of view.

383
00:22:50,520 --> 00:22:53,430
伤亡最小  对他们能力的冲击最大
Minimal loss of life, maximal impact on capability.

384
00:22:53,430 --> 00:22:56,160
要么全面开战  要么就不打
It's either total war or nothing at all.

385
00:22:58,030 --> 00:23:00,560
这可不符合外交策略  凯茜
Well, that doesn't sound very diplomatic, Cathy.

386
00:23:00,560 --> 00:23:02,790
我们要和恐怖分子谈外交吗
We're going to be diplomatic with terrorists?

387
00:23:02,790 --> 00:23:04,970
我向马克宗总统承诺过
I made a promise to President Makhzun.

388
00:23:04,970 --> 00:23:08,080
你之前就违背过诺言  这次有什么不同
You've broken promises before. Why should this be any different?

389
00:23:10,740 --> 00:23:13,310
不如我们休息一下  晚餐之后继续吧
Why don't we break for dinner? We'll pick this up afterwards.

390
00:23:13,310 --> 00:23:14,570
我想再考虑一下
I wanna review this a bit more.

391
00:23:14,570 --> 00:23:16,440
我会让人把食物送去罗斯福室
I'll have some food brought into the Roosevelt Room.

392
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:18,080
感谢各位
Thank you all very much.

393
00:23:21,990 --> 00:23:24,430
凯茜  我们俩就在这里吃吧
Cathy, why don't you and I eat in here?

394
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:43,480
"要么全面开战  要么就不打"
"Total war or nothing at all"?

395
00:23:44,340 --> 00:23:46,230
如果我在镜头前说
The moment I get in front of those cameras

396
00:23:46,230 --> 00:23:50,020
康威是对的  布洛哈特也是对的
and I tell them that Conway is right and Brockhart is right,

397
00:23:50,020 --> 00:23:53,540
你把哈里发国的事完全搞砸了
and that you completely bungled the ICO situation,

398
00:23:53,540 --> 00:23:55,660
你觉得邓巴到时会怎么样
how do you think Dunbar will do then?

399
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:03,420
请送两份科布沙拉过来  谢谢
Can we get two Cobb salads in here, please?

400
00:24:04,380 --> 00:24:07,640
-我不喜欢科布沙拉  -那你可以不吃
- I don't like Cobb salad. - Then you don't have to eat it.

401
00:24:12,910 --> 00:24:14,130
谢谢你过来
Thanks for coming over.

402
00:24:14,130 --> 00:24:16,190
我过来比你过去容易多了
Way easier coming here than you coming there.

403
00:24:16,190 --> 00:24:19,150
我门外有十支新闻团队守着呢
Must be ten news crews outside of my house.

404
00:24:19,150 --> 00:24:20,280
你怎么跑出来的
How'd you escape?

405
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:22,140
老办法  走后门
The old-fashioned way. Back door.

406
00:24:22,410 --> 00:24:23,950
你怎么弄到我的住宅电话的
How did you get my home phone?

407
00:24:23,950 --> 00:24:25,320
老办法
Oh, old-fashioned way.

408
00:24:25,320 --> 00:24:26,690
《先驱报》的联络簿
Rolodex from the Herald.

409
00:24:27,940 --> 00:24:30,320
-跟我来  不会很久的  -好的
- Come with me. I won't keep you long. - Yeah.

410
00:24:31,250 --> 00:24:34,390
-这些花了你多少时间  -几个月
- How long did this take you? - Couple of months.

411
00:24:34,760 --> 00:24:35,980
我单独做的
I've been working on my own.

412
00:24:36,150 --> 00:24:38,330
我们有一整队人手  都没发现这个
We had a whole team and we didn't find this.

413
00:24:38,330 --> 00:24:41,400
你们或许没有深挖到贝茨市葡萄园
Well, you probably weren't digging as deep as the Bates City Vine.

414
00:24:42,770 --> 00:24:43,630
没有
No.

415
00:24:44,310 --> 00:24:46,540
我们把大部分精力放在追踪资金上了
We spent most of our energy tracking the money.

416
00:24:46,540 --> 00:24:48,880
我们应该更关注出行记录的
We should've been more focused on the travel logs.

417
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:51,390
我是和一个匹萨店的人聊了之后才想到的
I wouldn't have checked either until I spoke with a pizza guy.

418
00:24:51,530 --> 00:24:53,500
后来我想到  他们有可能篡改出行记录
Then I realized they might be manipulating the logs.

419
00:24:53,500 --> 00:24:55,380
于是你想到了拉尼根
Which gets you to Lanagin.

420
00:24:55,380 --> 00:24:57,810
还是不能证明他见了拉尼根
It still doesn't prove he met with Lanagin,

421
00:24:57,810 --> 00:25:00,100
但我不知道车队还能去哪
but I don't know where else that motorcade would've been heading.

422
00:25:00,320 --> 00:25:01,930
你打算把这个公开吗
Are you going public with this?

423
00:25:02,370 --> 00:25:05,050
我是可以  但是他可以合理推诿
I could, but he has some plausible deniability.

424
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:07,460
全都推到密查姆身上
He pins it all on Meechum.

425
00:25:07,460 --> 00:25:08,830
如果他掩盖了行踪
If he's covering up travel,

426
00:25:08,830 --> 00:25:10,880
谁知道他还掩盖了什么
who knows what else he's covering up?

427
00:25:11,420 --> 00:25:12,850
那才是我想要的报道
That's the story I want,

428
00:25:12,850 --> 00:25:15,620
而不是什么特勤局人员不守纪律
not some Secret Service man being loose with the books.

429
00:25:16,490 --> 00:25:18,270
那你还没有引起注意
So you're still under the radar.

430
00:25:22,600 --> 00:25:24,720
我得请你对这一切保密
I have to ask you to keep all this to yourself.

431
00:25:25,260 --> 00:25:28,220
我知道你现在有了机会  这很诱人
I know it can be tempting now that... you have a chance,

432
00:25:28,220 --> 00:25:31,170
但如果这一切过早公布  他会提高警惕
but if this goes public too early, his guard goes up.

433
00:25:32,070 --> 00:25:35,140
我退出选举的时候很艰难
Listen, it was hard when I withdrew.

434
00:25:35,140 --> 00:25:37,730
领导层和公众对我的遗弃
How the leadership abandoned me, how the public did.

435
00:25:38,090 --> 00:25:39,130
花了些时间
It took some time... 

436
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:42,070
但我看开了
but I made my peace.

437
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,500
我是赢是输本来就不好说
It's a crapshoot whether I can win this.

438
00:25:44,500 --> 00:25:46,220
他可以反驳这样的报道
He can probably fight that off.

439
00:25:50,460 --> 00:25:53,390
你得写一篇他无法反驳的报道
You need to write the story that he can't fight off.

440
00:25:56,910 --> 00:26:00,310
你调查过他  突破点在哪里
You investigated him. Where's the weak link?

441
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:03,220
雷米·丹顿
Remy Danton.

442
00:26:28,390 --> 00:26:29,900
那是汤姆弄的
Tom did that.

443
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:35,330
真遗憾  他会合适你的
It's a shame. He'd be good for you.

444
00:26:39,620 --> 00:26:41,570
我从来没相信过牙仙
I never believed in the tooth fairy.

445
00:26:43,740 --> 00:26:45,870
但你还是把钱拿走了
Well, you took the money anyway.

446
00:26:47,270 --> 00:26:51,190
能帮我把那盏灯关了吗  很刺眼
Could you turn off that light, please? Hurts my eyes.

447
00:26:59,130 --> 00:27:02,870
你小时候  曾经
When you were small... you used to...

448
00:27:03,950 --> 00:27:07,750
曾经求我  让黑暗停止
used to ask me to make it stop, the dark.

449
00:27:07,750 --> 00:27:08,850
你还记得吗
Do you remember?

450
00:27:10,790 --> 00:27:11,780
记得
Yes.

451
00:27:12,780 --> 00:27:16,310
而我向你保证我会的  早上就让它停
And I promised you I would... in the morning.

452
00:27:19,580 --> 00:27:22,530
但该死的  你会每天晚上
But, damn it, you would sit at that window...

453
00:27:24,120 --> 00:27:25,200
一个人坐在窗前
every night...

454
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:30,020
想自己让太阳升起来
trying to make the sun rise, all by yourself.

455
00:27:33,630 --> 00:27:35,620
你脸靠在窗户上睡着后
Your daddy would put you in bed...

456
00:27:36,530 --> 00:27:41,320
你爸爸会把你抱上床
after you'd fallen asleep with your face against the glass.

457
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:46,260
我当时非常嫉妒
And I was so jealous.

458
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:49,060
嫉妒我和爸爸吗
Of me and Daddy?

459
00:27:50,810 --> 00:27:53,000
嫉妒你相信
That you believed.

460
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:58,100
你相信你可以让太阳升起
You believed you could make the sun rise.

461
00:28:03,060 --> 00:28:05,410
我跟护士谈了  母亲
I spoke to her, Mother, the nurse.

462
00:28:09,930 --> 00:28:11,090
我做不到
I can't do it.

463
00:28:12,010 --> 00:28:13,310
我做不到  母亲
I can't do it, Mother.

464
00:28:13,310 --> 00:28:15,250
我做不到你要我做的事
I can't do what you want me to do.

465
00:28:23,090 --> 00:28:24,030
克莱尔
Claire...

466
00:28:26,560 --> 00:28:28,400
你母亲去世
it'd help you win...

467
00:28:31,550 --> 00:28:33,410
会帮你赢的
having your mother gone.

468
00:28:38,660 --> 00:28:40,310
为我做这件事
Do this for me.

469
00:28:42,580 --> 00:28:44,790
让我最终能
And let me be a help to you.

470
00:28:45,990 --> 00:28:47,000
帮到你
Finally.

471
00:29:06,550 --> 00:29:07,500
汤姆
Tom.

472
00:29:11,350 --> 00:29:12,890
她想要你过去
She wants you to be there.

473
00:29:17,380 --> 00:29:18,350
你想要什么呢
What do you want?

474
00:29:23,010 --> 00:29:24,510
我也想要你过去
I want you to be there, too.

475
00:29:47,380 --> 00:29:48,330
好了
Okay.

476
00:32:25,690 --> 00:32:28,890
我告诉她是因为你让我别无选择
I told her because you put me in an impossible situation.

477
00:32:28,890 --> 00:32:31,470
她没有把柄  但你就是不听
There's nothing on her, but you wouldn't listen.

478
00:32:32,500 --> 00:32:35,340
那你来我家的时候肯定也没听进去
And you must not have listened when you came over to my house.

479
00:32:35,340 --> 00:32:36,780
我说得很清楚
I was very clear.

480
00:32:37,710 --> 00:32:41,270
那么  你又要把我丢到地上吗
So... you're gonna throw me on the ground again?

481
00:32:42,360 --> 00:32:44,380
看  这里有杯子  来吧
Look, here's a glass. Let's go ahead.

482
00:32:46,420 --> 00:32:47,520
你想把我炒掉吗
You wanna fire me?

483
00:32:48,770 --> 00:32:51,350
好啊  不就是又有人辞职吗
Fine. It's another resignation.

484
00:32:51,350 --> 00:32:53,980
在雷米  布洛哈特辞职之后
After Remy, after Brockhart.

485
00:32:53,980 --> 00:32:55,570
杜兰特和邓巴还虎视眈眈
With Durant, with Dunbar.

486
00:32:55,570 --> 00:32:56,840
我是靠编故事谋生的
You know, I spin stories for a living.

487
00:32:56,840 --> 00:32:59,110
我都形容不出这故事有多好拿来做文章
I can't begin to tell you how to spin this.

488
00:33:02,320 --> 00:33:05,190
你开小冰箱可不是为了拿健怡可乐
You know, the minibar wasn't open because you wanted a Diet Coke.

489
00:33:06,940 --> 00:33:08,600
我担心你  道格
I'm worried about you, Doug.

490
00:33:08,600 --> 00:33:10,260
我不需要人担心
Nobody needs to worry about me.

491
00:33:10,260 --> 00:33:11,480
你需要有人为你担心
Yeah, somebody does...

492
00:33:12,150 --> 00:33:15,470
因为这个焦土政策对我们很不好
because this scorched-earth policy is bad for us.

493
00:33:15,470 --> 00:33:19,120
我才不在乎莉安·哈维  我们需要她
I don't give a rat's ass about LeAnn Harvey. We need her.

494
00:33:19,780 --> 00:33:23,340
而你需要我  但我们都需要你
And you need me. And we both need you.

495
00:33:23,340 --> 00:33:25,000
-处在最好的状态  -我很好
- At your best. - I'm fine.

496
00:33:25,470 --> 00:33:28,520
是吗  你不让我控制损失
Are you? Instead of having me do damage control,

497
00:33:28,520 --> 00:33:30,480
反而让我伤害自己人
you're having me do damage to one of our own.

498
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:32,430
我是在保护总统
I am trying to protect the president.

499
00:33:32,430 --> 00:33:34,570
而我是在保护你
And I'm trying to protect you...

500
00:33:34,580 --> 00:33:35,620
免受自己的伤害
from yourself.

501
00:33:37,360 --> 00:33:40,260
你别瞎说了  你才不在乎我
You're so full of shit. You don't care about me.

502
00:33:41,630 --> 00:33:44,340
你干了那种事  我本应该恨你
After what you did, I should hate you.

503
00:33:46,260 --> 00:33:47,870
但那样能给我们带来什么呢
But where does it get us?

504
00:33:59,460 --> 00:34:00,750
看一下《电讯报》吧
Check out the Telegraph.

505
00:34:02,390 --> 00:34:03,930
策略起效了
The strategy is working...

506
00:34:04,850 --> 00:34:05,890
如果你肯的话
if you let it.

507
00:34:07,440 --> 00:34:09,650
或者逼我辞职  你决定
Or make me resign. Your call.

508
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:46,140
{\an8}佩特罗夫:  杜兰特不是救市和约旦河谷事件中的关键人物

509
00:34:46,140 --> 00:34:47,820
{\an8}安东尼·莫雷蒂纪念基金

510
00:34:57,820 --> 00:34:58,930
{\an8}捐款

511
00:35:22,140 --> 00:35:24,350
{\an8}道格拉斯·斯坦普

512
00:35:30,700 --> 00:35:33,280
{\an8}谢谢
您的5000美元捐款已接收

513
00:35:46,740 --> 00:35:49,790
-你还好吗  -那是她想要的
- Are you okay? - It's what she wanted.

514
00:35:49,790 --> 00:35:51,290
我在问你
I was asking you.

515
00:35:52,110 --> 00:35:53,350
把投票安排到明天
Schedule the vote for tomorrow.

516
00:35:53,350 --> 00:35:55,770
我会飞回去在投票前讲话
I'll fly back to speak just before.

517
00:35:55,770 --> 00:35:57,080
克莱尔  你母亲刚刚去世了
Claire, your mother just passed.

518
00:35:57,080 --> 00:35:58,570
安排一下  弗兰西斯
Schedule it, Francis. 

519
00:35:58,890 --> 00:36:00,920
汤姆写了一篇讲稿  很不错
Tom wrote a speech. It's good.

520
00:36:02,700 --> 00:36:05,600
-凯茜还没同意  -那就逼她同意
- Cathy's not on board yet. - Then get her on board.

521
00:36:07,210 --> 00:36:08,190
我很抱歉
I'm sorry.

522
00:36:09,290 --> 00:36:10,840
-我不是...  -不不  没关系
- I didn't mean to-- - No, no, it's all right.

523
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:11,900
我会搞定
I'll get it done.

524
00:36:12,140 --> 00:36:14,870
谢谢  明天见
Thank you. I'll see you tomorrow.

525
00:36:14,870 --> 00:36:15,780
晚安
Good night.

526
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:19,710
让杜兰特国务卿到总统办公室见我
Ask Secretary Durant to meet me in the Oval. 

527
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:20,400
好的  先生
Yes, sir.

528
00:36:27,510 --> 00:36:28,920
总统先生
Mr. President.

529
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:32,660
在咖啡桌上
Coffee table.

530
00:36:33,310 --> 00:36:37,060
{\an8}佩特罗夫:  杜兰特不是救市和约旦河谷事件中的关键人物

531
00:36:36,970 --> 00:36:39,250
有趣的是我都没让他这么做
The funny thing is I didn't even have to ask him to do it.

532
00:36:39,250 --> 00:36:40,850
他自己做的
He did it on his own.

533
00:36:41,640 --> 00:36:43,530
我尤其喜欢他说
I especially like where he says,

534
00:36:43,530 --> 00:36:45,610
"凯瑟琳·杜兰特堪用
"Catherine Durant is functional.

535
00:36:45,730 --> 00:36:48,210
克莱尔·安德伍德强大"
Claire Underwood is formidable."

536
00:36:54,540 --> 00:36:58,490
你看  时间没有站在你那边  而在我们这边
So, you see, you don't even have time on your side. It's on ours.

537
00:36:58,490 --> 00:37:01,030
到明天早上  会有十几篇类似报道
By tomorrow morning, there'll be a dozen articles just like that.

538
00:37:01,030 --> 00:37:02,470
所以你可以做选择
So you have a choice.

539
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:04,750
你可以选择在接下来四年中继续当国务卿
You can redeem yourself as Secretary of State

540
00:37:04,750 --> 00:37:06,510
重树形象
over the next four years,

541
00:37:06,510 --> 00:37:10,090
或选择因为在中东办砸了事
or go down in history as a fluke, who bungled the Middle East

542
00:37:10,090 --> 00:37:13,330
连勃兰登堡的协议都谈不成而被载入史册
and couldn't even close the deal in Brandenburg.

543
00:37:13,330 --> 00:37:15,360
你有你的版本  我也有我的
You have your version. I have mine.

544
00:37:15,730 --> 00:37:18,460
我相信我的版本会跟这个一样引人注目
I'm sure mine will get just as much traction as this.

545
00:37:18,460 --> 00:37:21,860
但是我的版本会赢  因为这样报道更有意思
But my version wins because it's the better story...

546
00:37:21,860 --> 00:37:24,830
并且事情也确实如此
and it's also exactly how things went down.

547
00:37:25,550 --> 00:37:28,210
你看连真相都不向着你
You see, you don't even have the truth going for you.

548
00:37:29,360 --> 00:37:31,050
我不怕你
I'm not scared of you.

549
00:37:32,640 --> 00:37:37,160
我背书邓巴  会是一篇更好的报道
My endorsement of Dunbar, that makes for an even better story.

550
00:37:40,580 --> 00:37:43,250
但你知道最棒的报道是什么吗
But you wanna know what the best story is?

551
00:37:46,630 --> 00:37:49,120
克莱尔的母亲刚刚去世了
Claire's mother just died.

552
00:37:49,980 --> 00:37:53,010
-我很遗憾  -我想你不是真心的
- I'm sorry to hear that. - Oh, I don't think you really are,

553
00:37:53,010 --> 00:37:56,400
不过没关系  反正全世界除了你都会难过
but that doesn't matter because the rest of the world will.

554
00:37:56,400 --> 00:37:59,000
等她明晚做完讲话
And by the time she gives her speech tomorrow night,

555
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:01,310
亚特兰大乃至全国的观众
there won't be a dry eye in Atlanta

556
00:38:01,310 --> 00:38:03,860
都会为之动容而落泪
or across the rest of the country.

557
00:38:04,290 --> 00:38:07,990
你可以保住你的工作  凯茜  
So, you get to keep your job, Cathy, 

558
00:38:08,180 --> 00:38:10,090
换你代表的票
in return for your delegates.

559
00:38:10,090 --> 00:38:11,870
我的提议依然有效
That offer is still on the table.

560
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:16,040
我一直很忠诚  我帮你得到这个位置
I have been loyal. I got you that table.

561
00:38:16,380 --> 00:38:19,980
你想继续守住  还是想拱手让给康威
Do you wanna keep it, or do you wanna give it to Conway?

562
00:38:27,540 --> 00:38:29,920
我在等移植手术的时候
You know, when I was waiting for my transplant,

563
00:38:29,920 --> 00:38:34,020
我产生了特别逼真的幻觉  你都不会相信
I had the most vivid hallucinations. You wouldn't believe 'em.

564
00:38:34,020 --> 00:38:35,670
你知道我看到谁了吗
Do you know who I saw?

565
00:38:36,960 --> 00:38:40,870
彼得·罗素和佐伊·巴恩斯  就在这个办公室里
Peter Russo and Zoe Barnes, right here in this room.

566
00:38:40,870 --> 00:38:44,370
佐伊就在这张沙发上引诱我
Zoe was trying to seduce me, right here on this couch,

567
00:38:44,370 --> 00:38:49,480
而彼得把我的脸按在这块玻璃上
and Peter, he shoved my face up against this glass.

568
00:38:50,100 --> 00:38:53,380
香烟  剃须刀片和性爱
Cigarettes and razor blades and sex.

569
00:38:54,220 --> 00:38:55,590
很可怕
It was terrifying.

570
00:38:56,900 --> 00:38:58,680
我只想逃出这间
All I wanted to do was get out of this room

571
00:38:58,680 --> 00:39:00,750
我费劲千辛万苦才进来的房间
that I worked so hard to get in.

572
00:39:02,980 --> 00:39:05,250
但它们阴魂不散是有道理的
But of course, it makes sense that they would've haunted me

573
00:39:05,250 --> 00:39:07,710
因为全都是真的
because it's all true.

574
00:39:08,970 --> 00:39:12,530
-什么是真的  -卢卡斯·古德温所说的一切
- What is? - Everything Lucas Goodwin claimed.

575
00:39:12,530 --> 00:39:15,460
我杀了他们两个  就像他说的那样
I killed them both, just like he said I did.

576
00:39:16,730 --> 00:39:21,070
但当然没人会相信  永远不会有人相信
But of course, nobody believes it, and nobody ever will.

577
00:39:21,720 --> 00:39:23,840
因为我们就是那么擅长
Because that's how good we are...

578
00:39:25,550 --> 00:39:27,420
让东西
at making things...

579
00:39:28,750 --> 00:39:30,170
消失
disappear.

580
00:39:40,430 --> 00:39:43,460
不  我们没杀过人
No, we didn't kill anybody.

581
00:39:47,160 --> 00:39:48,510
但如果需要
But we would have...

582
00:39:49,980 --> 00:39:51,560
我们会的
if it was necessary.

583
00:39:53,110 --> 00:39:56,170
你说得对  谈判的时间结束了
So, you're right, the time for negotiations is over.

584
00:39:56,170 --> 00:39:57,910
你要交出你的代表
You will hand over your delegates,

585
00:39:57,910 --> 00:40:00,350
继续在我的内阁任职
and you will serve on in my cabinet.

586
00:40:00,350 --> 00:40:03,500
我们忘掉发生过的这一切
And we will forget that any of this ever happened.

587
00:40:05,520 --> 00:40:07,500
因为如果你不照做
Because if you don't...

588
00:40:10,770 --> 00:40:12,570
我向上帝发誓
I swear to God...

589
00:40:14,540 --> 00:40:16,270
我永远
I will never...

590
00:40:17,590 --> 00:40:20,870
都不会忘记
ever forget.

591
00:40:24,970 --> 00:40:27,520
现在你明白了吗
Do you understand now?

592
00:40:34,320 --> 00:40:35,330
明白
Yes.

593
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:51,610
好
Good.

594
00:40:52,320 --> 00:40:55,730
我们去决定要怎么对付恐怖分子吧
Now, let's go decide what we're gonna do about these terrorists.

595
00:41:39,430 --> 00:41:42,940
想让我给谁打电话吗  做些安排
Want me to call someone? Make arrangements?

596
00:42:55,780 --> 00:42:57,470
我们让太阳升起来了
We made the sun rise.

597
00:42:59,820 --> 00:43:01,400
她也告诉你了
She told you that, too? 

598
00:43:33,880 --> 00:43:35,140
我们该动身了
We should get going.

599
00:44:55,840 --> 00:44:58,570
我和汉娜想向第一夫人和总统
Me and Hannah want to extend our warmest condolences

600
00:44:58,570 --> 00:45:01,170
致以最诚挚的哀悼
to the First Lady and the President.

601
00:45:01,170 --> 00:45:05,660
我们为他们和伊丽莎白·黑尔的亲人们祈祷
They and all of Elizabeth Hale's loved ones are in our prayers.

602
00:45:05,660 --> 00:45:08,890
出于对离世之人的尊敬  今天我们不竞选
And we won't be campaigning today out of respect for their loss.

603
00:45:08,900 --> 00:45:11,550
愿上帝保佑总统夫妇
God bless President and Mrs. Underwood.

604
00:45:12,560 --> 00:45:13,520
好了
Got it.

605
00:45:14,470 --> 00:45:15,460
发布吧
Put it out.

606
00:45:15,910 --> 00:45:19,100
她倒毙的时机掐得真好
Perfect timing... for her to drop dead.

607
00:45:19,450 --> 00:45:20,890
我们本来正顺风顺水呢
We were on a roll, too.

608
00:45:40,790 --> 00:45:42,420
我该准备讲话了
I should prep for the speech.

609
00:45:42,420 --> 00:45:45,120
我为你准备好了房间  我马上就过去
I have a room set up for you. I'll be right in.

610
00:45:45,500 --> 00:45:46,970
这边请  安德伍德夫人
Right this way, Mrs. Underwood.

611
00:45:51,380 --> 00:45:52,680
我读过草稿了
I read the draft.

612
00:45:53,930 --> 00:45:54,850
然后呢
And?

613
00:45:55,370 --> 00:45:58,780
-一个字都不用改  -我很高兴你满意
- I wouldn't change a thing. - I'm glad you're pleased.

614
00:45:59,550 --> 00:46:01,180
我很高兴你陪着她
I'm glad you were with her.

615
00:46:01,610 --> 00:46:03,930
她很坚强  你很幸运
She's strong. You're a lucky man.

616
00:46:05,070 --> 00:46:06,330
完全同意
Don't I know it.

617
00:46:12,410 --> 00:46:15,940
女士们先生们  我很荣幸为大家介绍
Ladies and gentlemen, it is a great honor to introduce

618
00:46:15,940 --> 00:46:18,880
国务卿凯瑟琳·杜兰特
Secretary of State Catherine Durant.

619
00:46:36,510 --> 00:46:38,710
谢谢  非常感谢大家
Thank you, thank you very much.

620
00:46:39,890 --> 00:46:43,900
我知道  大家和我一样
I know that all of you join me in offering

621
00:46:43,900 --> 00:46:48,920
都对第一夫人亲人的离世表示诚挚慰唁
our sincere condolences to the First Lady for her loss.

622
00:46:51,450 --> 00:46:57,150
今晚  我想向在代表大会上
Tonight, I want to offer my sincere gratitude

623
00:46:57,150 --> 00:47:01,060
支持我的各位代表
to all the delegates who have honored me with their support

624
00:47:01,060 --> 00:47:02,950
致以我最真挚的感谢
during the course of this convention.

625
00:47:02,950 --> 00:47:04,610
我非常感谢你们
Thank you so much.

626
00:47:07,510 --> 00:47:13,290
{\an8}民主党全国代表大会

627
00:47:12,320 --> 00:47:16,570
然而  经过深思熟虑
However, after much deliberation...

628
00:47:17,570 --> 00:47:23,050
我决定  与辞职参加选举相比  作为国务卿
I have decided that I have more to offer you as Secretary of State

629
00:47:23,050 --> 00:47:26,340
我能更好地为大家服务
than to resign and run for office.

630
00:47:29,080 --> 00:47:33,130
但我想让支持我的各位
But I want to encourage every one of you who has supported me

631
00:47:33,130 --> 00:47:38,120
和我一起支持这位非凡的女性
to join me in supporting this extraordinary woman,

632
00:47:38,120 --> 00:47:42,380
美国第一夫人  克莱尔·黑尔·安德伍德
the First Lady of the United States, Claire Hale Underwood.

633
00:48:05,630 --> 00:48:06,610
谢谢
Thank you.

634
00:48:09,760 --> 00:48:10,690
谢谢
Thank you.

635
00:48:12,640 --> 00:48:13,890
晚上好
And good evening.

636
00:48:15,460 --> 00:48:17,930
正如大家所知  我母亲
As all of you know, my mother, 

637
00:48:17,930 --> 00:48:20,040
伊丽莎白·康斯坦斯·黑尔
Elizabeth Constance Hale,

638
00:48:20,400 --> 00:48:24,490
久病后于昨晚去世
passed away last night after a long illness.

639
00:48:26,760 --> 00:48:29,020
她是个坚强的女人...
She was a strong woman...

640
00:48:29,600 --> 00:48:31,150
一个坚韧的德州人
a fierce Texan...

641
00:48:35,630 --> 00:48:42,550
从小...我和她关系就不好
We had... a difficult relationship from childhood onwards.

642
00:48:43,750 --> 00:48:47,000
我们曾有过很长时间的疏离
At times, there were long periods of estrangement.

643
00:48:48,150 --> 00:48:53,120
我们经常深深地伤害对方
We hurt each other... often and deeply.

644
00:48:54,350 --> 00:48:57,980
如果说母亲的病带来什么好事  那就是
If there was one good thing that came from my mother's illness...

645
00:48:59,770 --> 00:49:04,720
让我们有机会重新开始往来  抚平旧伤
it gave us a chance to reconnect, to mend old wounds.

646
00:49:05,710 --> 00:49:07,520
人们并不是都能
And that's not an opportunity

647
00:49:07,520 --> 00:49:10,060
在父母离世前有这样的机会
people always get before a parent dies,

648
00:49:10,060 --> 00:49:12,260
我很感激有这样的机会
and I'm grateful to have had that.

649
00:49:15,580 --> 00:49:17,140
那我在这里做什么呢
And what am I doing here?

650
00:49:21,770 --> 00:49:25,850
我站在这里  因为这是我母亲所希望的
I'm here because my mother wanted me to be.

651
00:49:27,830 --> 00:49:30,010
昨天在她去世之前  她对我说
Yesterday, before she passed, she said to me,

652
00:49:30,020 --> 00:49:32,860
"克莱尔...去做吧
"Claire... do this.

653
00:49:33,610 --> 00:49:37,010
如果这是人们希望的  听他们的
If the people want it, listen to them.

654
00:49:37,830 --> 00:49:39,840
如果失败了  那就是失败了
And if you lose, then you lose.

655
00:49:40,770 --> 00:49:42,120
但是如果你赢了...
But if you win...

656
00:49:46,350 --> 00:49:49,310
要感到荣幸  保持谦逊
be honored, be humbled, 

657
00:49:49,310 --> 00:49:51,900
和弗兰西斯一起赢得选举"
and win this election with Francis!"

658
00:50:00,670 --> 00:50:03,180
我告诉她  康威夫妇是非常厉害的对手
And I told her, I said, "The Conways are tough opponents."

659
00:50:03,190 --> 00:50:06,930
她说也许是吧  但也不比德州人
And she said, "They may be tough, but they're not Texas tough."

660
00:50:11,620 --> 00:50:14,490
失去让我们深思
Loss is a sobering phenomenon.

661
00:50:15,140 --> 00:50:18,020
几个月前  我差点失去了我的丈夫
Several months ago, I almost lost my husband.

662
00:50:18,410 --> 00:50:21,310
我们的国家差点失去了总统
Our nation almost lost a President.

663
00:50:23,180 --> 00:50:26,590
失去让我们重新审视我们珍惜的一切
Loss makes us reevaluate what we hold dear.

664
00:50:28,100 --> 00:50:29,890
我还想告诉你们...
And I'll tell you, there were...

665
00:50:31,160 --> 00:50:33,280
就在不久之前
times in the not too distant past,

666
00:50:33,280 --> 00:50:38,270
弗兰西斯和我...差点失去我们的婚姻
where Francis and I, we... almost lost our marriage.

667
00:50:39,750 --> 00:50:42,540
我们遇到了困难  还以为坚持不下去了
Hard times when we thought we wouldn't make it.

668
00:50:43,740 --> 00:50:44,950
正如很多人知道的
And like many of you know,

669
00:50:44,950 --> 00:50:47,550
婚姻并非总是一帆风顺
marriage isn't always the smoothest road.

670
00:50:48,700 --> 00:50:52,070
是一个精神错乱的年轻人让我记起
And it took the actions of a deranged young man

671
00:50:52,230 --> 00:50:55,810
弗兰西斯对我有多重要
to remind me how important Francis is to me.

672
00:50:57,960 --> 00:51:01,240
现在  我的母亲去世了...
And now, with my mother gone...

673
00:51:04,430 --> 00:51:06,920
他就是我唯一的亲人了
he's the only family I have left.

674
00:51:08,090 --> 00:51:12,300
我愿把我的人生  我们的国家和未来
I trust Francis Underwood with my life,

675
00:51:12,670 --> 00:51:16,060
托付给弗兰西斯·安德伍德
with our nation, with our future.

676
00:51:16,820 --> 00:51:18,720
我希望你们也能信任他
I hope you will, too.

677
00:51:24,210 --> 00:51:28,300
如果你们信任我们  我会谨遵母亲的话
And if you trust the both of us, I'll heed my mother's words,

678
00:51:28,300 --> 00:51:32,120
如被提名为他的竞选伙伴  我将深感荣幸
and I'll be honored if you nominate me as his running mate.

679
00:51:42,920 --> 00:51:52,920
克莱尔  克莱尔  克莱尔
Claire! Claire! Claire!

680
00:51:54,430 --> 00:51:57,330
天呐  你真棒
Jesus! You did great work.

681
00:52:08,480 --> 00:52:09,610
女士们先生们...
Ladies and gentlemen...

682
00:52:14,070 --> 00:52:17,350
秘书长女士  作为党代会主席
Madam Secretary, as Convention Chair,

683
00:52:17,690 --> 00:52:19,300
我提议通过口头表决提名
I move that we make the nomination

684
00:52:19,300 --> 00:52:21,820
克莱尔·安德伍德竞选副总统...
of Claire Underwood for Vice President...

685
00:52:22,240 --> 00:52:25,850
弗兰西斯·安德伍德竞选总统
and Francis Underwood for President by acclamation.

686
00:52:38,950 --> 00:52:44,290
对总统和副总统的提名
Do I hear a second to vote by acclamation

687
00:52:44,290 --> 00:52:47,560
进行口头表决  是否有人附议
for the nomination of the President and the Vice President?

688
00:52:47,560 --> 00:52:49,870
-说得好  -提议通过
- Hear, hear! - So moved.

689
00:52:50,480 --> 00:52:54,430
赞成提名
All of those in favor of the nomination

690
00:52:54,430 --> 00:52:55,790
弗兰斯西·安德伍德
of Francis Underwood for

691
00:52:55,790 --> 00:52:59,110
竞选美国总统的说赞成
President of the United States, say "Aye."

692
00:52:59,110 --> 00:53:02,580
-赞成  -反对提名的
- Aye! - All those against.

693
00:53:02,580 --> 00:53:03,550
反对
Nay!

694
00:53:03,550 --> 00:53:08,020
赞成提名克莱尔·安德伍德
All those in favor of the nomination of Claire Underwood

695
00:53:08,020 --> 00:53:11,770
竞选美国副总统的说赞成
for our Vice President of the United States, say "Aye."

696
00:53:11,770 --> 00:53:13,740
赞成
Aye!

697
00:53:13,740 --> 00:53:16,080
-反对提名的  -反对
- Against? - Nay!

698
00:53:16,320 --> 00:53:18,310
赞成者占多数
The Ayes have it!

699
00:53:24,380 --> 00:53:29,660
本党决定2016年总统选举候选人为
Our party's ticket for the 2016 Presidential Election

700
00:53:29,660 --> 00:53:33,560
弗兰西斯和克莱尔·安德伍德
will be Francis and Claire Underwood!

701
00:53:54,990 --> 00:53:57,010
{\an8}民主党全国代表大会  安德伍德夫妇获取民主党提名

